{"title_page": "Zolki Band", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Zolki Band\n| image           = Zolki_Band.jpg\n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = Zolki Band in 2019 (from left to right: shell, kukuruzo, trikil, f.s.t., green)\n| caption         = Zolki Band in 2019 (from left to right: shell, kukuruzo, trikil, f.s.t., green)\n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = \n| genre           = [[Indie rock]], [[Alternative rock]]\n| years_active    = <!-- {{start date|YYYY}}\u2013{{end date|YYYY}} (or \u2013present) --> {{Start date|2013}}\u2013present\n| label           = \n| associated_acts = Daj Darohu ({{lang-ru|\u0414\u0430\u0439 \u0414\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0433\u0443}}), Intra muros, D_tails, Vertigo Band, Funny House, \u041a\u043b\u0435\u0439, Terrakod\n| website         = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} or {{Official URL}} -->\n| current_members = shell<br/>green<br/>kukuruzo<br/>trikil<br/>f.s.t.\n| past_members    = rotten\n| module          = \n| module2         = \n| module3         = \n}}\n'''Zolki Band''' is a [[Belarus]]ian indie rock band from [[Brest, Belarus|Brest]], which was founded in 2013 by former members of the Daj Darohu ({{lang-ru|\u0414\u0430\u0439 \u0414\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0433\u0443}}), Intra muros, and D_tails bands. \n\n== History ==\nThe band's first single \u201c''\u015anie\u017ea\u0144\u201d'' ({{trans|December}}) topped the charts for the 2013\u201314 season of the music portal [[Tuzin.fm]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tuzinfm.by/article/1116/piesniaj-sezonu-2014-stala-refleksija-na-ploscu-2010.html|title=\u041f\u0435\u0441\u044c\u043d\u044f\u0439 \u0441\u044d\u0437\u043e\u043d\u0443-2014 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0440\u044d\u0444\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0456\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u041f\u043b\u043e\u0448\u0447\u0443-2010|last=Tuzin.fm|first=|date=2014-08-18|website=|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009062556/https://tuzinfm.by/article/1116/piesniaj-sezonu-2014-stala-refleksija-na-ploscu-2010.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> The song was recorded in collaboration with the Landau band and is dedicated to [[2010 Belarusian presidential election#Protests and crackdown|the civil protests in Minsk]] taken place in December 2010 and the following crackdown.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tuzinfm.by/performer/mp3/867/sniezan.html|title=Landau. \u0420\u044d\u0444\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0456\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u043c\u0440\u043e\u0447\u043d\u044b \u0441\u044c\u043d\u0435\u0436\u0430\u043d\u044c-2010 (\u0430\u045e\u0434\u044b\u0451)|last=Tuzin.fm|first=|date=2014-05-14|website=|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009062921/https://tuzinfm.by/performer/mp3/867/sniezan.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> \n\nIn 2014 Zolki Band released its debut album ''Do\u016dhi do\u016dhi dzie\u0144'' supported with music videos for songs \u201c''Rak\u201d'' and \u201c''B.E.Z.R.A.Z.L.I.C.H.I.E. \u2014 heta tradycyja.\u201d''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.experty.by/content/zolki-band-zap-sal-albom-pra-seks-pal-tyku-slukhatsspampavats|title=Zolki Band \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0456\u0441\u0430\u043b\u0456 \u0430\u043b\u044c\u0431\u043e\u043c \u043f\u0440\u0430 \u0441\u044d\u043a\u0441 \u0456 \u043f\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0442\u044b\u043a\u0443 (+\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0445\u0430\u0446\u044c/+\u0441\u043f\u0430\u043c\u043f\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0446\u044c)|last=\u0427\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0443\u0445\u0430|first=\u0410\u043b\u044f\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440|date=2014-12-18|access-date=2019-10-09|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009130127/http://www.experty.by/content/zolki-band-zap-sal-albom-pra-seks-pal-tyku-slukhatsspampavats|archive-date=2019-10-09|publisher=[[Experty.by]]|work=[[Ultra-music.com]]|publication-date=|language=be|ssrn=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tuzinfm.by/albums/1727/nie-zahasnuc-zolki-u-niebie.html|title=\u041d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0441\u043d\u0443\u0446\u044c Zolki \u045e \u043d\u0435\u0431\u0435|last=\u0411\u0443\u0434\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439|date=2015-02-13|website=|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|others=|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009130326/https://tuzinfm.by/albums/1727/nie-zahasnuc-zolki-u-niebie.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> Later that year the band was nominated in the category of \u201cOpening of the Year\u201d at the \u201cHeroes of the Year Awards\u201d (presented by [[Tuzin.fm]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tuzinfm.by/article/2591/sort-list-muzycnaj-premiji-hieroji-hodu-2015-naminacyja.html|title=\u0428\u043e\u0440\u0442-\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u0447\u043d\u0430\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u044d\u043c\u0456\u0456 \u00ab\u0413\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0456 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0443 \u2014 2015\u00bb. \u041d\u0430\u043c\u0456\u043d\u0430\u0446\u044b\u044f \u00ab\u0410\u0434\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0446\u044c\u0446\u0451 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0443\u00bb|last=Tuzin.fm|first=|date=2015-11-19|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009065016/https://tuzinfm.by/article/2591/sort-list-muzycnaj-premiji-hieroji-hodu-2015-naminacyja.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=161686|title=\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d.FM \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u045e \u0433\u0435\u0440\u043e\u044f\u045e \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u0424\u041e\u0422\u0410\u0420\u042d\u041f\u0410\u0420\u0422\u0410\u0416|last=tuzin.fm|first=|last2=\u041d\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0430\u045e|first2=\u041c\u0456\u043a\u0456\u0442\u0430|date=2015-12-13|website=|publisher=[[Nasha Niva]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009065157/https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=161686|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019 Zolki Band released a music video for the song \u201c''Drevy i cieni\u201d'' ({{trans|Trees and Shadows}}) dedicated to protests against the construction of the [[China|Chinese]]-funded lead-acid battery factory near Brest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mediabrest.by/news/kultura/brestskaya-gruppa-vypustila-klip-protiv-akkumulyatornogo-zavoda|title=\u0411\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0440\u0443\u043f\u043f\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u043f\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u0430\u043a\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0430|last=|first=|date=2019-05-13|website=|publisher=[[\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0430\u0411\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009130612/https://mediabrest.by/news/kultura/brestskaya-gruppa-vypustila-klip-protiv-akkumulyatornogo-zavoda|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> Also the release of the second album was announced, the first part of which entitled \u201c''\u0160ort \u0160ort Night, Pt. 1\u201d'' was subsequently released on September 15, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tuzinfm.by/albums/4500/sort-sort-night-pt-1.html|title=\u041c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u044b\u0436\u0430\u043d\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0444\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044b\u043a\u0430. zolki band \u0440\u0432\u0435 \u0448\u0430\u0431\u043b\u043e\u043d\u044b|last=TuzinFM|first=|date=2019-09-30|website=|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009061719/https://tuzinfm.by/albums/4500/sort-sort-night-pt-1.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref>\n\n== Band members ==\n* shell \u2014 drums\n* green \u2014 bass guitar\n* kukuruzo \u2014 acoustic guitar, keyboards, backing vocals\n* trikil \u2014 guitar, keyboards, backing vocals\n* f.s.t. \u2014 lead vocals \n\n;Production\n* dizel \u2014 sound engineer\n;Former members\n* rotten \u2014 guitar\n\n== Discography ==\n;Studio albums\n* 2014 - ''Do\u01d4hi do\u01d4hi dzie\u0144''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://budzma.by/news/nye-zahasnuc-zolki-w-nyebye.html|title=\u041d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0441\u043d\u0443\u0446\u044c Zolki \u045e \u043d\u0435\u0431\u0435|last=\u0411\u0443\u0434\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439|date=2015-01-16|language=be|publisher=[[Budzma Belarusians!]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322223041/http://budzma.by/news/nye-zahasnuc-zolki-w-nyebye.html|archivedate=2019-03-22|accessdate=2020-03-02}}</ref>\n* 2019 - ''\u0160ort \u0160ort Night, Pt. 1''\n\n;EPs, singles, lives\n* 2013 - ''\u015anie\u017ea\u0144'' (single, together with Landau)\n* 2015 - ''Choladna z vami'' (EP)\n* 2016 - ''Kvazi\u010calaviek'' (single)\n* 2017 - ''Kaliadny ra\u01d4t'' (live)\n* 2018 - ''Zolki Band \u0443 Belsat Music Live'' (live)\n* 2019 - ''Drevy i cieni'' (single)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://zolkiband.bandcamp.com Official page on Bandcamp]\n\n[[Category:Belarusian indie rock groups]]\n[[Category:Belarusian rock music groups]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Zolki Band\n| image           = Zolki_Band.jpg\n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = Zolki Band in 2019 (from left to right: shell, kukuruzo, trikil, f.s.t., green)\n| caption         = Zolki Band in 2019 (from left to right: shell, kukuruzo, trikil, f.s.t., green)\n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = \n| genre           = [[Indie rock]], [[Alternative rock]]\n| years_active    = <!-- {{s