0 \u0437\u043c\u0440\u043e\u0447\u043d\u044b \u0441\u044c\u043d\u0435\u0436\u0430\u043d\u044c-2010 (\u0430\u045e\u0434\u044b\u0451)|last=Tuzin.fm|first=|date=2014-05-14|website=|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009062921/https://tuzinfm.by/performer/mp3/867/sniezan.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> \n\nIn 2014 Zolki Band released its debut album ''Do\u016dhi do\u016dhi dzie\u0144'' supported with music videos for songs \u201c''Rak\u201d'' and \u201c''B.E.Z.R.A.Z.L.I.C.H.I.E. \u2014 heta tradycyja.\u201d''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.experty.by/content/zolki-band-zap-sal-albom-pra-seks-pal-tyku-slukhatsspampavats|title=Zolki Band \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0456\u0441\u0430\u043b\u0456 \u0430\u043b\u044c\u0431\u043e\u043c \u043f\u0440\u0430 \u0441\u044d\u043a\u0441 \u0456 \u043f\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0442\u044b\u043a\u0443 (+\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0445\u0430\u0446\u044c/+\u0441\u043f\u0430\u043c\u043f\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0446\u044c)|last=\u0427\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0443\u0445\u0430|first=\u0410\u043b\u044f\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440|date=2014-12-18|access-date=2019-10-09|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009130127/http://www.experty.by/content/zolki-band-zap-sal-albom-pra-seks-pal-tyku-slukhatsspampavats|archive-date=2019-10-09|publisher=[[Experty.by]]|work=[[Ultra-music.com]]|publication-date=|language=be|ssrn=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tuzinfm.by/albums/1727/nie-zahasnuc-zolki-u-niebie.html|title=\u041d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0441\u043d\u0443\u0446\u044c Zolki \u045e \u043d\u0435\u0431\u0435|last=\u0411\u0443\u0434\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439|date=2015-02-13|website=|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|others=|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009130326/https://tuzinfm.by/albums/1727/nie-zahasnuc-zolki-u-niebie.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> Later that year the band was nominated in the category of \u201cOpening of the Year\u201d at the \u201cHeroes of the Year Awards\u201d (presented by [[Tuzin.fm]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tuzinfm.by/article/2591/sort-list-muzycnaj-premiji-hieroji-hodu-2015-naminacyja.html|title=\u0428\u043e\u0440\u0442-\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u0447\u043d\u0430\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u044d\u043c\u0456\u0456 \u00ab\u0413\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0456 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0443 \u2014 2015\u00bb. \u041d\u0430\u043c\u0456\u043d\u0430\u0446\u044b\u044f \u00ab\u0410\u0434\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0446\u044c\u0446\u0451 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0443\u00bb|last=Tuzin.fm|first=|date=2015-11-19|work=[[Budzma Belarusians!]]|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009065016/https://tuzinfm.by/article/2591/sort-list-muzycnaj-premiji-hieroji-hodu-2015-naminacyja.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=161686|title=\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d.FM \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u045e \u0433\u0435\u0440\u043e\u044f\u045e \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u0424\u041e\u0422\u0410\u0420\u042d\u041f\u0410\u0420\u0422\u0410\u0416|last=tuzin.fm|first=|last2=\u041d\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0430\u045e|first2=\u041c\u0456\u043a\u0456\u0442\u0430|date=2015-12-13|website=|publisher=[[Nasha Niva]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009065157/https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=161686|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019 Zolki Band released a music video for the song \u201c''Drevy i cieni\u201d'' ({{trans|Trees and Shadows}}) dedicated to protests against the construction of the [[China|Chinese]]-funded lead-acid battery factory near Brest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mediabrest.by/news/kultura/brestskaya-gruppa-vypustila-klip-protiv-akkumulyatornogo-zavoda|title=\u0411\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0440\u0443\u043f\u043f\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u043f\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u0430\u043a\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0430|last=|first=|date=2019-05-13|website=|publisher=[[\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0430\u0411\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009130612/https://mediabrest.by/news/kultura/brestskaya-gruppa-vypustila-klip-protiv-akkumulyatornogo-zavoda|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> Also the release of the second album was announced, the first part of which entitled \u201c''\u0160ort \u0160ort Night, Pt. 1\u201d'' was subsequently released on September 15, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tuzinfm.by/albums/4500/sort-sort-night-pt-1.html|title=\u041c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u044b\u0436\u0430\u043d\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0444\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044b\u043a\u0430. zolki band \u0440\u0432\u0435 \u0448\u0430\u0431\u043b\u043e\u043d\u044b|last=TuzinFM|first=|date=2019-09-30|website=|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009061719/https://tuzinfm.by/albums/4500/sort-sort-night-pt-1.html|archive-date=2019-10-09|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref>\n\n== Band members ==\n* shell \u2014 drums\n* green \u2014 bass guitar\n* kukuruzo \u2014 acoustic guitar, keyboards, backing vocals\n* trikil \u2014 guitar, keyboards, backing vocals\n* f.s.t. \u2014 lead vocals \n\n;Production\n* dizel \u2014 sound engineer\n;Former members\n* rotten \u2014 guitar\n\n== Discography ==\n;Studio albums\n* 2014 - ''Do\u01d4hi do\u01d4hi dzie\u0144''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://budzma.by/news/nye-zahasnuc-zolki-w-nyebye.html|title=\u041d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0441\u043d\u0443\u0446\u044c Zolki \u045e \u043d\u0435\u0431\u0435|last=\u0411\u0443\u0434\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439|date=2015-01-16|language=be|publisher=[[Budzma Belarusians!]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322223041/http://budzma.by/news/nye-zahasnuc-zolki-w-nyebye.html|archivedate=2019-03-22|accessdate=2020-03-02}}</ref>\n* 2019 - ''\u0160ort \u0160ort Night, Pt. 1''\n\n;EPs, singles, lives\n* 2013 - ''\u015anie\u017ea\u0144'' (single, together with Landau)\n* 2015 - ''Choladna z vami'' (EP)\n* 2016 - ''Kvazi\u010calaviek'' (single)\n* 2017 - ''Kaliadny ra\u01d4t'' (live)\n* 2018 - ''Zolki Band \u0443 Belsat Music Live'' (live)\n* 2019 - ''Drevy i cieni'' (single)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://zolkiband.bandcamp.com Official page on Bandcamp]\n\n[[Category:Belarusian indie rock groups]]\n[[Category:Belarusian rock music groups]]\n", "name_user": "Pr12402", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zolki_Band"}
{"title_page": "GL Music", "text_new": "'''GL Music Entertainment A/S''' is a label, publishing & TV Production company representing some of the leading Scandinavian songwriters, artists, musicians and producers as well as some of the world's leading independent music publishers.\n\n'''GL Music Entertainment A/S''' was founded in 2006 and has been working with the leading Scandinavian and international independent and major labels, television stations and film companies regarding songwriting, production and album releases for various artists, TV series, movies etc.\n\nThey are a Copenhagen-based Scandinavian team and since the start they have participated in no. 1 singles/albums, success TV shows and blockbuster Movies. They have produced and written songs for various gold and platinum selling artists and their songs have sold more than 30 million physical albums and singles around the world and a lot of streams.\n\n'''GL Music Entertainment''' is in charge of Musical Direction on TV talent shows like [[The X Factor|X-Factor]], Mentor, LIVE, Talent and Voice Junior on national TV in Denmark. In 2015 they founded a TV production department focusing on music TV content and formats. The first production was the 24 episode \u2018Rasmus Klump Julestue\u2019 in collaboration with Egmont Kids Publishing.\n\n'''GL Music Entertainment's''' publishing department also represent and sub-publish some amazing catalogs of songs in Scandinavia from publishers all over the world. These catalogs include Cloud 9 Music (Netherlands), The Royalty Network (US), Roba Music Publishing (Germany), PEN Music Group (US), A&G Sync (UK), Memory Lane Music Group (US), Red Brick Songs (Canada), Casablanca Media Publishing (Canada), Schedler Music (Austria), Css Rights Management (Canada), 120 Publishing (Australia) and great hit songs from artists like Johnny Cash, Elvis Presley, Corinne Bailey Rae to big DJ superstars like David Guetta, Lost Frequencies, Amin Van Buuren, Hardwell, Felix Jahn and many more.\n\n'''GL Music Entertainment''' has 6 recording studios with state of the art equipment.\n\nGL Music Entertainment is 100% independent and owned by [https://www.linkedin.com/in/lasse-lindorff-73a260/?locale=de_DE Lasse Lindorff], Daniel F\u00e4lt and Kim Nowak-Zorde\n\n==Working with Artists, Producers and Songwriters like==\n\n*Boye & Sigvardt (DJ/Producers) \n*Askling (Artist) \n*[[Afrojack]] (DJ/Producer) \n*[[Alok (DJ)|Alok]] (DJ/Producer)\n*[[Angel Janson]] (Artist/Producer)\n*Kasper \"Kay\" Larsen (Producer/Songwriter)\n*Karen Rosenberg (Artist/Songwriter) \n*K\u00e9work (Producer/Songwriter)\n*[[Kill the Buzz|Kill The Buzz]] (DJ/Producer)\n*Frank Pole (DJ/Producer) \n*[[Wafande]] (Artist/Songwriter) \n*Martin Luke Brown (Artist/Songwriter) \n*Andreas Ringblom (Producer/Songwriter) \n*Lasse Lindorff (Producer/Songwriter) \n*Frederik Leopold (Artist/Songwriter)\n*Daniel F\u00e4lt  (Producer) \n*Frederik Jyll (Producer/Songwriter) \n*David West (Artist/Songwriter)\n*Max Ulver (Artist/Songwriter) \n*Kim Nowak-Zorde (Songwriter) \n*Johnny Deluxe (Artist) \n*Shoko (Artist) \n*Tom&Jame (DJ/Producer)\n*Tony Cornelissen (Songwriter)\n*Uhre (Artist) \n*Vinze (DJ/Producer) \n*Mosimann (DJ/Producer) \n*Ilang (Artist/Songwriter) \n*Emilio (Artist) \n*Ghourilla (Artist)\n*Rekesh Dukaloo (Producer)\n*Belmin Kuburas (Artist)\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.glmusic.dk/ Official website]\n\n[[Category:Danish record producers]]\n[[Category:Danish songwriters]]\n", "text_old": "'''GL Music Entertainment A/S''' is a label, publishing & TV Production company representing some of the leading Scandinavian songwriters, artists, musicians and producers as well as some of the world's leading independent music publishers.\n\n'''GL Music Entertainment A/S''' was founded in 2006 and has been working with the leading Scandinavian and international independent and major labels, television stations and film companies regarding songwriting, production and album releases for various artists, TV series, movies etc.\n\nThey are a Copenhagen-based Scandinavian team and since the start they have participated in no. 1 singles/albums, success TV shows and blockbuster Movies. They have produced and written songs for various gold and platinum selling artists and their songs have sold more than 30 million physical albums and singles around the world and a lot of streams.\n\n'''GL Music Entertainment''' is in charge of Musical Direction on TV talent shows like [[The X Factor|X-Factor]], Mentor, LIVE, Talent and Voice Junior on national TV in Denmark. In 2015 they founded a TV production department focusing on music TV content and formats. The first production was the 24 episode \u2018Rasmus Klump Julestue\u2019 in collaboration with Egmont Kids Publishing.\n\n'''GL Music Entertainment's''' publishing department also represent and sub-publish some amazing catalogs of songs in Scandinavia from publishers all over the world. These catalogs include Cloud 9 Music (Netherlands), The Royalty Network (US), Roba Music Publishing (Germany), PEN Music Group (US), A&G Sync (UK), Memory Lane Music Group (US), Red Brick Songs (Canada), Casablanca Media Publishing (Canada), Schedler Music (Austria), Css Rights Management (Canada), 120 Publishing (Australia) and great hit songs from artists like Johnny Cash, Elvis Presley, Corinne Bailey Rae to big DJ superstars like David Guetta, Lost Frequencies, Amin Van Buuren, Hardwell, Felix Jahn and many more.\n\n'''GL Music Entertainment''' has 6 recording studios with state of the art equipment.\n\nGL Music Entertainment is 100% independent and owned by [https://www.linkedin.com/in/lasse-lindorff-73a260/?locale=de_DE Lasse Lindorff], Daniel F\u00e4lt and Kim Nowak-Zorde\n\n==Working with Artists, Producers and Songwriters like==\n\n*Boye & Sigvardt (DJ/Producers) \n*Askling (Artist) \n*[[Afrojack]] (DJ/Producer) \n*[[Angel Janson]] (Artist/Producer)\n*Kasper \"Kay\" Larsen (Producer/Songwriter)\n*Karen Rosenberg (Artist/So