-list/ |title=Emmys 2019: Game of Thrones Ties Record and Leads TV Pack; Fleabag, Chernobyl and Mrs. Maisel Win Big |first=Matt Webb |last=Mitovich |website=TVLine |date=September 22, 2019 |accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series\n| Jason Bateman (for \"Reparations\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series]]\n| Laura Linney (for \"One Way Out\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series]]\n| Julia Garner (for \"The Gold Coast\")\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series\n| Jason Bateman (for \"Reparations\")\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[71st Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards|Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards]]\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Casting for a Drama Series|Outstanding Casting for a Drama Series]]\n| Alexa L. Fogel, Tara Feldstein Bennett, and Chase Paris\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"4\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/09/2019-creative-arts-emmys-winners-list-1202173604/ |title=Complete Creative Arts Emmy Awards 2019 Winners List: 'Game of Thrones' Torches Competitors |first=Libby |last=Hill |website=IndieWire |date=September 14, 2019 |accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Outstanding Production Design for a Narrative Contemporary Program (One Hour or More)\n| [[Derek R. Hill]], John Richardson, and Kim Leoleis (for \"Outer Darkness\", \"The Gold Coast\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Single-Camera Picture Editing for a Drama Series|Outstanding Single-Camera Picture Editing for a Drama Series]]\n| Cindy Mollo and Heather Goodwin (for \"One Way Out\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Sound Mixing for a Comedy or Drama Series (One-Hour)|Outstanding Sound Mixing for a Comedy or Drama Series (One-Hou